  More actions
  
  Add this to `~/.zshrc`:
  
  ```
  function toggle-transient-prompt() {
    (( ${+functions[p10k]} )) || return
    if [[ ${POWERLEVEL9K_TRANSIENT_PROMPT-} == off ]]; then
      typeset -g POWERLEVEL9K_TRANSIENT_PROMPT=always
    else
      typeset -g POWERLEVEL9K_TRANSIENT_PROMPT=off
    fi
    p10k reload
    if zle; then
      zle push-input
      zle accept-line
    fi
  }
  ```
  
  Invoke this function by typing `toggle-transient-prompt`. You can also bind it to a key by adding two more lines to `~/.zshrc`:
  
  ```
  # Bind Ctrl-T to toggle powerlevel10k transient prompt.
  zle -N toggle-transient-prompt
  bindkey '^T' toggle-transient-prompt
  ```
  
